party: [Entity executing the contract; must provide valid legal name, jurisdiction, and authorized representative.]
effective_date: [Contract commencement date, ISO-standard YYYY-MM-DD.]
recitals: [
    Articulate factual reasons and mutual objectives for entering the agreement.
    Must include: business rationale, scope, and strategic purpose.
]
definitions: [
    Explicitly list and clarify every key term (e.g., "Services," "IP," "Confidential Information").
    Include any industry, regulatory, or custom interpretations.
]
services_provided: [
    Detailed enumeration of deliverables, including milestones, technical specs, and performance criteria.
]
payment_terms: [
    Specify: amounts, due dates, invoicing protocols, payment methods (e.g., ACH, wire), late fees, audit rights.
]
confidentiality_clause: [
    Prohibit disclosure of specified confidential information.
    Define duration of confidentiality, allowable disclosures (if any), and remedies for breach.
]
intellectual_property_clause: [
    All work is company-owned (state: "company is sole and exclusive owner of all deliverables and inventions").
    Employee assigns all present and future rights.
    All works within contract scope are considered “works for hire.”
    Employee is required to promptly disclose all inventions.
    Employee must execute further documents perfecting rights.
]
warranty_clause: [
    Provider warrants no known infringement of third-party IP.
    Include explicit disclaimer of implied warranties (merchantability, fitness, etc.).
    Knowledge-qualified warranty applies only to known issues at time of execution.
]
indemnity_clause: [
    Provider defends customer against all third-party IP claims
    Provider responsible for all damages, costs, settlements within defined scope (trade secret, patent, copyright, trademark).
    Indemnity triggered when a third-party claim is formally filed.
    No indemnity for customer misuse.
    Expressly include a cap on provider’s liability (dollar amount, e.g., $1M; customizable).
    Customer must promptly notify provider of claim; parties cooperate in defense.
]
license_rights: [
    Research and confirm actual IP owner.
    Negotiate and memorialize scope of any licenses, if relevant.
    Must sign and record license agreements.
    Continuous monitoring and compliance verification required.
]
employee_obligations: [
    Immediate disclosure of inventions.
    Assignment of all rights and execution of all required documents.
    Warrant that no conflicts exist with other agreements/employment.
    Prohibit use of third-party IP unless authorized in writing.
]
termination_clause: [
    State valid conditions for termination (for cause, convenience, breach).
    Specify notice period (e.g., 30 days).
    List all surviving clauses/rights post-termination.
]
dispute_resolution: [
    Mandatory mediation step before any litigation.
    Specify legal jurisdiction, venue.
    Winner awarded attorney fees.
]
amendment_procedure: [
    Changes only valid if in writing and signed by authorized representatives of both parties.
]
force_majeure: [
    No liability for events outside reasonable control (natural disaster, war, government action).
]
signatures: [
    Physical or electronic signatures required.
    Must include dates, printed names, titles.
]
jurisdiction: [
    Specify exclusive court system/location for all disputes (e.g., State of Delaware).
]
remedies_for_breach: [
    Damages, specific performance, and contract termination as cumulative potential remedies.
]
assignment_of_agreement: [
    State whether rights/obligations may be assigned or transferred; require prior written consent if restricted.
]
notice_methods: [
    List valid delivery channels (email, registered mail, courier); designate recipient contacts/addresses.
]
governing_law: [
    Specify state or country governing law.
]
attachments_and_exhibits: [
    List and reference all supplemental documents (schedules, specifications, statements of work).
]
boilerplate_clauses: [
    Entire agreement: supersedes all prior written/oral agreements.
    Severability: unenforceable clause does not invalidate remainder.
    Headings: descriptive only, do not affect interpretation.
]
compliance_statement: [
    Each party warrants ongoing compliance with all applicable local, state, federal, and international laws, regulations.
    Immediate notification required upon discovery of non-compliance.
]
audit_rights: [
    Company reserves right to inspect, audit, and verify compliance at scheduled or random intervals.
]
exclusivity_clause: [
    Supplier agrees to exclusive supply, prohibiting sales to competitors or other unauthorized entities.
]
non_compete_clause: [
    Employee/contractor prohibited from providing similar services to competitors for X years post-termination.
    Specify geographic scope, duration, and permitted exceptions.
]
IP_monitoring: [
    Automated searches on the internet and social media for company IP (logos, text, trademarks).
    Google Alerts and similar services set for relevant keywords.
    Social profile scans performed for unauthorized use.
    DMCA and cease & desist requests initiated if infringement detected.
]
data_protection: [
    All personal data processed in strict accordance with applicable law (e.g., GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA).
    Privacy policy required and referenced (URL).
]
trade_secret_provision: [
    Mandatory secure storage of trade secrets.
    Limit disclosure to authorized persons on need-to-know basis.
    Immediate injunctive relief/remedy for breach.
]
contract_compliance_check: [
    Random automated compliance audits scheduled through the lifecycle of the agreement.
]
